1
00:00:50,047 --> 00:00:52,038
(distant siren)

2
00:01:00,287 --> 00:01:02,278
(water dripping)

3
00:01:03,527 --> 00:01:06,087
(man) Cecilia was the first to go.

4
00:01:06,167 --> 00:01:08,158
(siren approaches)

5
00:01:09,807 --> 00:01:12,162
(voices over two-way radio)

6
00:01:30,487 --> 00:01:32,478
(siren starts)

7
00:01:39,167 --> 00:01:41,158
(heart monitor beeping)

8
00:01:47,407 --> 00:01:49,716
What are you doing here, honey?

9
00:01:49,807 --> 00:01:53,004
You're not even old enough
to know how bad life gets.

10
00:01:53,087 --> 00:01:56,716
Obviously, Doctor,
you've never been a 1 3-year-old girl.

11
00:02:30,487 --> 00:02:33,285
Everyone dates
the demise of our neighbourhood...

12
00:02:33,367 --> 00:02:35,881
..from the suicides of the Lisbon girls.

13
00:02:36,847 --> 00:02:40,920
People saw their clairvoyance in
the wiped-out elms, the harsh sunlight...

14
00:02:41,007 --> 00:02:44,204
..and the continuing decline
of our auto industry.

15
00:02:44,647 --> 00:02:48,435
Even then, as teenagers,
we tried to put the pieces together.

16
00:02:48,727 --> 00:02:50,957
We still can't.

17
00:02:51,047 --> 00:02:54,198
Now whenever we run into each other
at lunches or parties...

18
00:02:54,287 --> 00:02:57,404
..we find ourselves going over
the evidence one more time.

19
00:02:57,487 --> 00:03:00,559
All to understand those five girls,...

20
00:03:00,647 --> 00:03:04,276
..who, after all these years,
we can't get out of our minds.

21
00:03:06,407 --> 00:03:08,796
Cecilia, the youngest, was 1 3.

22
00:03:11,807 --> 00:03:14,401
And Lux was 1 4.

23
00:03:16,367 --> 00:03:18,881
Bonnie was 1 5.

24
00:03:18,967 --> 00:03:21,356
Mary was 1 6.

25
00:03:23,887 --> 00:03:26,276
And Therese was 1 7.

26
00:03:29,327 --> 00:03:33,081
No one could understand how Mrs Lisbon
and Mr Lisbon, our math teacher,...

27
00:03:33,167 --> 00:03:35,840
..had produced such beautiful creatures.

28
00:03:38,247 --> 00:03:42,081
Paul Baldino claimed to have
found Cecilia on her first attempt.

29
00:03:42,167 --> 00:03:44,237
Hey, l was the one who found her.

30
00:03:45,167 --> 00:03:48,557
l was in the storm sewer under my house.
There's all these tunnels.

31
00:03:48,647 --> 00:03:50,638
You could get into anyone's house.

32
00:03:50,727 --> 00:03:52,718
When Paul said this, we believed him...

33
00:03:52,807 --> 00:03:55,799
..because he was the son
of Sammy ''the Shark'' Baldino,...

34
00:03:55,887 --> 00:03:58,196
..and we knew about his escape tunnel.

35
00:03:58,287 --> 00:04:01,916
So l went up, thinking l could see
one of those girls taking a shower!

36
00:04:02,007 --> 00:04:03,406
Right!

37
00:04:03,487 --> 00:04:05,205
And l walk in...

38
00:04:05,287 --> 00:04:07,005
..and l see blood everywhere.

39
00:04:07,247 --> 00:04:11,240
So l turned around, went for the stairs
and right back out the tunnel.

40
00:04:11,887 --> 00:04:13,878
l had to tell you guys that story.

41
00:04:14,367 --> 00:04:16,483
l'll see you guys later, all right?

42
00:04:19,167 --> 00:04:23,126
- (woman) l heard there was an accident.
- (woman #2) lt was no accident, Joan.

43
00:04:23,207 --> 00:04:25,402
Of course the parents are to blame!

44
00:04:25,927 --> 00:04:28,202
l heard they found the razor in the toilet...

45
00:04:28,287 --> 00:04:31,836
Everyone had an opinion
as to why Cecilia had tried to kill herself.

46
00:04:32,447 --> 00:04:35,883
That girl didn't want to die.
She just wanted out of that house.

47
00:04:35,967 --> 00:04:38,561
She wanted out
of that decorating scheme.

48
00:04:42,287 --> 00:04:45,882
The most popular theory
held Dominic Palazzolo to blame.

49
00:04:46,287 --> 00:04:51,202
Dominic was staying with relatives
until his family got settled in New Mexico.

50
00:04:51,287 --> 00:04:54,404
He was the first in our neighbourhood
to wear sunglasses,...

51
00:04:54,487 --> 00:04:57,206
..and within a week of his arrival
he'd fallen in love.

52
00:04:58,327 --> 00:05:02,115
The object of his desire wasn't Cecilia,
but Diana Porter.

53
00:05:07,087 --> 00:05:08,645
l love her!

54
00:05:08,727 --> 00:05:12,879
When Diana Porter left on vacation
in Switzerland, Dominic denounced God.

55
00:05:14,447 --> 00:05:16,438
To prove the validity of his love...

56
00:05:16,527 --> 00:05:19,883
..he jumped off the roof
of his relatives' house.

57
00:05:41,487 --> 00:05:43,921
Ahem! l'm gonna
show you some images,...

58
00:05:44,527 --> 00:05:47,360
..and, uh... you tell me...

59
00:05:49,367 --> 00:05:51,358
..what they remind you of.

60
00:05:52,687 --> 00:05:54,279
OK?

61
00:06:10,287 --> 00:06:12,278
A banana.

62
00:06:17,687 --> 00:06:19,678
A swamp.

63
00:06:28,207 --> 00:06:30,004
An Afro.

64
00:06:47,927 --> 00:06:50,885
l don't think Cecilia
truly meant to end her life.

65
00:06:52,327 --> 00:06:54,318
Her act was a cry for help.

66
00:06:55,527 --> 00:06:57,518
l know you're very strict,...

67
00:06:57,607 --> 00:07:02,317
..but l think that Cecilia would benefit
by having a social outlet...

68
00:07:02,407 --> 00:07:05,160
..outside of the codification of school,...

69
00:07:06,527 --> 00:07:09,917
..where she could interact
with males her own age.

70
00:07:16,887 --> 00:07:21,802
Peter Sisten had helped Mr Lisbon install
a model of the solar system in his class.

71
00:07:21,887 --> 00:07:24,799
And in return Mr Lisbon
invited him for dinner.

72
00:07:24,887 --> 00:07:27,196
Bless us, O Lord, and these thy gifts,...

73
00:07:27,287 --> 00:07:31,121
..which we are about to receive from thy
bounty, through Christ our Lord. Amen.

74
00:07:31,407 --> 00:07:32,806
Amen.

75
00:07:32,887 --> 00:07:35,481
Lux, please, put your shirt on this instant.

76
00:07:35,567 --> 00:07:37,558
(whispers) Sorry.

77
00:07:40,967 --> 00:07:43,800
- Thank you, dear.
- Can you pass the salt, please?

78
00:07:43,887 --> 00:07:46,606
- Ham?
- Thank you.

79
00:07:46,687 --> 00:07:49,599
- Sweetheart, would you like some peas?
- l hate peas.

80
00:07:49,687 --> 00:07:50,881
Here.

81
00:07:51,607 --> 00:07:54,041
(father) That's a nice-looking ham, dear.

82
00:07:56,167 --> 00:07:59,000
- Well, thank you, honey.
- (girl) Mm, this is good.

83
00:07:59,087 --> 00:08:02,079
So, Peter, are you an aviation enthusiast?

84
00:08:02,647 --> 00:08:07,084
Well, l don't know if l'd call myself
an enthusiast, but l like planes.

85
00:08:09,087 --> 00:08:10,679
Ah.

86
00:08:10,767 --> 00:08:14,316
Uh, Peter, are you on the football squad?

87
00:08:14,847 --> 00:08:17,680
Um, no, l play it,
but l'm not actually on the team.

88
00:08:17,767 --> 00:08:19,962
- Oh, l see.
- (father) Ah, not a team player.

89
00:08:20,047 --> 00:08:21,639
Do you like to wrestle?

90
00:08:22,927 --> 00:08:26,078
- (girls laugh)
- (father) You OK, Peter?

91
00:08:26,167 --> 00:08:30,797
The Brazilian turbot frog was added to
the endangered species list today.

92
00:08:31,287 --> 00:08:33,801
- That's the third animal this year.
- Oh, dear.

93
00:08:33,887 --> 00:08:36,685
The turbot frog?
l don't think l've ever heard of...

94
00:08:36,767 --> 00:08:38,962
Um, excuse me, may l use the rest room?

95
00:08:39,047 --> 00:08:42,039
Oh, of course. The one down here
isn't working very well.

96
00:08:42,127 --> 00:08:45,324
- Go upstairs through Cecilia's room.
- OK. Thanks.

97
00:09:50,527 --> 00:09:52,722
- (knocking)
- Hold... Hold on.

98
00:09:53,607 --> 00:09:56,121
(giggles) l thought you'd died in there.

99
00:09:57,367 --> 00:10:00,643
Are you done hogging the bathroom?
l need something.

100
00:10:07,807 --> 00:10:09,604
Do you mind?

101
00:10:12,407 --> 00:10:13,806
(giggles)

102
00:10:17,367 --> 00:10:20,677
- Thank you very much.
- You forgetting something?

103
00:10:23,327 --> 00:10:26,717
Oh, Peter. Here's a little aerofoil
l thought you might find amusing.

104
00:10:26,807 --> 00:10:28,638
lt's a...

105
00:10:28,727 --> 00:10:32,083
..demonstration of
Bernoulli's principle: lift.

106
00:10:35,087 --> 00:10:38,045
From that time on,
the Lisbon house began to change.

107
00:10:41,447 --> 00:10:43,677
Almost every day,...

108
00:10:43,767 --> 00:10:46,645
..and even when
she wasn't keeping an eye on Cecilia,...

109
00:10:46,727 --> 00:10:49,116
..Lux would suntan wearing a swimsuit...

110
00:10:49,207 --> 00:10:54,361
..that caused the knife sharpener to give
her a 1 5-minute demonstration for free.

111
00:10:57,287 --> 00:11:01,166
Following the doctor's orders,
two weeks after Cecilia returned home...

112
00:11:01,247 --> 00:11:06,037
..Mr Lisbon persuaded his wife to allow
the girls to throw the first and only party...

113
00:11:06,127 --> 00:11:07,924
..of their short lives.

114
00:11:16,527 --> 00:11:18,518
There. ls that OK?

115
00:11:20,287 --> 00:11:22,278
l'm gonna get dressed.

116
00:11:30,927 --> 00:11:33,282
- Welcome!
- Good evening, Mrs Lisbon.

117
00:11:33,367 --> 00:11:35,358
Come on in.

118
00:11:37,927 --> 00:11:39,997
The party's in the basement.

119
00:11:42,847 --> 00:11:46,522
Just go on round to the left,
and then down the stairs.

120
00:11:47,167 --> 00:11:49,476
(mellow middle-of-the-road music )

121
00:11:58,767 --> 00:12:00,519
Hi, l'm Bonaventure.

122
00:12:00,607 --> 00:12:01,562
Hi.

123
00:12:01,647 --> 00:12:03,638
- Hi. Tim.
- Nice to meet you.

124
00:12:05,287 --> 00:12:06,686
Hi.

125
00:12:09,207 --> 00:12:11,357
- Would you like some punch?
- Yeah.

126
00:12:12,327 --> 00:12:13,521
Thanks.

127
00:12:13,607 --> 00:12:15,598
- Hi.
- Hi.

128
00:12:16,247 --> 00:12:18,044
Thanks.

129
00:12:18,727 --> 00:12:20,718
- Hi.
- Thank you.

130
00:12:23,327 --> 00:12:25,124
- Hey.
- Hi.

131
00:12:25,207 --> 00:12:27,004
Do you wanna sit down?

132
00:12:27,087 --> 00:12:29,282
- Yeah.
- Me too.

133
00:12:50,967 --> 00:12:52,764
(nervous laughter)

134
00:13:09,007 --> 00:13:10,998
Um, how did your SATs go?

135
00:13:11,807 --> 00:13:13,445
OK.

136
00:13:13,527 --> 00:13:15,324
Good.

137
00:13:16,007 --> 00:13:18,316
Do you know where you're applying yet?

138
00:13:18,807 --> 00:13:22,243
Well, no, but my parents
are pushing towards Yale...

139
00:13:22,327 --> 00:13:24,318
..cos that's where my dad went.

140
00:13:25,687 --> 00:13:27,678
That's nice.

141
00:13:30,087 --> 00:13:32,476
You have to imagine
what it'd be like when...

142
00:13:32,567 --> 00:13:36,480
..out of the sun would come the Hun
and his Messerschmitt coming down.

143
00:13:36,567 --> 00:13:39,320
And boys, l swear,
two or three years older than you...

144
00:13:39,407 --> 00:13:43,116
..would be in this - the P51 B Mustang.
B for what? For bull's-eye, see?

145
00:13:45,687 --> 00:13:47,279
You've heard of Yale?

146
00:13:47,367 --> 00:13:49,358
Oh, yeah.

147
00:13:50,527 --> 00:13:52,245
This punch is fantastic.

148
00:13:52,327 --> 00:13:54,921
- Can l give you more?
- Sure. What's in it?

149
00:13:56,127 --> 00:13:58,960
Juices. Some cherry, pineapple.

150
00:13:59,887 --> 00:14:03,004
You know, l uh... l love pineapple.

151
00:14:04,687 --> 00:14:06,279
Really?

152
00:14:15,127 --> 00:14:19,837
This baby would come in, and this won
the war for the United Kingdom. You see?

153
00:14:20,567 --> 00:14:22,762
- Excuse me.
- Sure.

154
00:14:23,407 --> 00:14:27,844
And it's this kind of, uh...
this kind of equipment that makes, uh...

155
00:14:27,927 --> 00:14:30,122
..a model work.

156
00:14:31,647 --> 00:14:33,638
Here's Joe.

157
00:14:35,207 --> 00:14:37,198
- Hi, Joe.
- Hi.

158
00:14:39,727 --> 00:14:43,925
- Now, if he needs anything just call me.
- Oh, l'm sure he'll be fine.

159
00:14:44,767 --> 00:14:46,166
Hi.

160
00:14:47,167 --> 00:14:48,998
Hi.

161
00:14:49,087 --> 00:14:52,363
- Joe! Good to see you. How are ya?
- Hey, Joe.

162
00:14:52,447 --> 00:14:55,166
- Glad you came tonight.
- How's it going?

163
00:14:55,247 --> 00:14:57,044
You're just in time.

164
00:14:57,567 --> 00:14:58,966
Good. Hi.

165
00:14:59,047 --> 00:15:01,845
Everyone look! His ears wiggle
if you scratch his chin.

166
00:15:01,927 --> 00:15:03,326
(laughter)

167
