- (cheering)
- Good job, Joe!

172
00:15:20,967 --> 00:15:22,958
(boy) Good job, Joe.

173
00:15:23,047 --> 00:15:25,242
(* The Hollies.: ''The Air That l Breathe'')

174
00:15:25,327 --> 00:15:27,557
Where'd you learn that song?

175
00:15:28,927 --> 00:15:30,918
May l be excused?

176
00:15:31,327 --> 00:15:34,876
lf you want to, dear, but this is your party.

177
00:15:37,447 --> 00:15:41,645
Oh, all right, if you want to go upstairs,
go ahead, but we'll just...

178
00:15:41,727 --> 00:15:44,241
We'll just have to have fun without you.

179
00:15:45,007 --> 00:15:47,521
Oh, look. He always chooses heads.

180
00:15:47,607 --> 00:15:49,598
- Joe, what's it gonna be?
- Heads.

181
00:15:49,687 --> 00:15:51,962
Joe, will you try tails?

182
00:15:53,327 --> 00:15:54,919
Heads it is!

183
00:15:55,007 --> 00:15:57,202
l'll show you again. Let's go.

184
00:15:57,287 --> 00:15:58,879
- Heads.
- Tails.

185
00:15:58,967 --> 00:16:00,161
Heads.

186
00:16:00,247 --> 00:16:02,841
- One more time. ln the air, Joe.
- Heads.

187
00:16:06,327 --> 00:16:08,716
Heads it is anyway. One more time here.

188
00:16:08,807 --> 00:16:11,002
- OK, call in the air, Joe.
- Heads.

189
00:16:12,327 --> 00:16:14,397
Heads. Not bad.

190
00:16:16,527 --> 00:16:18,358
How you doin'?

191
00:16:18,447 --> 00:16:20,244
Good.

192
00:16:20,927 --> 00:16:24,124
- You picked it up really well.
- lt's my favourite song.

193
00:16:24,847 --> 00:16:27,156
You know, you're... very beautiful.

194
00:16:28,927 --> 00:16:30,918
l could paint you sometime.

195
00:16:32,327 --> 00:16:34,124
Thanks.

196
00:16:38,727 --> 00:16:40,843
- So did they sing it to you?
- Yeah.

197
00:16:40,927 --> 00:16:42,918
(voices and laughter)

198
00:16:44,007 --> 00:16:46,601
(Mr Lisbon) Cecilia!

199
00:16:46,687 --> 00:16:48,678
(startled cries)

200
00:16:49,367 --> 00:16:51,403
Cecilia!

201
00:16:52,247 --> 00:16:54,238
(gasps)

202
00:17:07,207 --> 00:17:09,277
Oh, my God...

203
00:17:09,367 --> 00:17:12,325
No! No! No! Don't look. Turn around.

204
00:17:14,127 --> 00:17:16,436
Turn around. Darlings, turn around.

205
00:17:16,527 --> 00:17:19,280
Don't look. Don't... Don't look at this.

206
00:17:19,887 --> 00:17:22,355
Oh, Jesus. Please, God.

207
00:17:23,327 --> 00:17:26,285
(Mrs Lisbon wails and sobs)

208
00:18:40,527 --> 00:18:42,404
OK.

209
00:18:53,687 --> 00:18:56,201
- What did he say?
- He said she was only 1 3.

210
00:18:58,247 --> 00:19:00,238
(door bell)

211
00:19:09,687 --> 00:19:12,042
Oh, hi, Mary. Are your parents home?

212
00:19:12,127 --> 00:19:14,118
Hi, Father Moody. Come in.

213
00:19:21,407 --> 00:19:23,398
Oh, hello, Father.

214
00:19:24,927 --> 00:19:26,918
Please, sit down.

215
00:19:27,487 --> 00:19:29,557
Thanks.

216
00:19:29,647 --> 00:19:31,717
Come on, Miller, that was inside.

217
00:19:33,567 --> 00:19:35,558
Ah, no. No, thanks.

218
00:19:38,527 --> 00:19:40,324
(gulps)

219
00:19:44,127 --> 00:19:47,802
How about we get the missus down here,
have a little chat?

220
00:19:47,887 --> 00:19:49,878
Afraid she's under the weather.

221
00:19:49,967 --> 00:19:52,686
(clears throat) She's not really...

222
00:19:53,167 --> 00:19:55,158
..seeing anybody.

223
00:19:57,047 --> 00:19:59,242
Well, she'll see her priest.

224
00:19:59,607 --> 00:20:03,839
Ah! This kid's a sucker
for the high inside ones every time.

225
00:20:03,927 --> 00:20:05,918
Every time.

226
00:20:06,407 --> 00:20:08,477
Excuse me.

227
00:20:11,167 --> 00:20:13,158
Father.

228
00:20:17,927 --> 00:20:21,124
Ah! Double play... Father.

229
00:20:23,007 --> 00:20:24,998
Double play.

230
00:20:46,247 --> 00:20:48,238
Mrs Lisbon?

231
00:20:55,687 --> 00:20:57,279
(knocks)

232
00:20:57,367 --> 00:20:59,756
- May l come in?
- (girl) OK.

233
00:21:03,367 --> 00:21:05,358
Hello, girls.

234
00:21:05,967 --> 00:21:07,958
l thought we could talk.

235
00:21:08,847 --> 00:21:10,838
Do you feel like talking?

236
00:21:12,287 --> 00:21:16,200
Well, if you ever want to,
you know where to find me.

237
00:21:25,687 --> 00:21:27,678
Mrs Lisbon, it's Father Moody.

238
00:21:33,567 --> 00:21:35,762
Mrs Lisbon, hello.

239
00:21:39,367 --> 00:21:44,566
l wanted you to know that
l listed Cecilia's death as an accident.

240
00:21:57,887 --> 00:22:02,199
An accident waiting to happen. John said
you couldn't get a policy to cover it.

241
00:22:02,287 --> 00:22:04,403
l know. lt's so incredibly dangerous.

242
00:22:04,487 --> 00:22:06,478
Let's give it a try.

243
00:22:09,367 --> 00:22:10,959
Ready?

244
00:22:11,047 --> 00:22:12,878
One, two, three.

245
00:22:16,447 --> 00:22:20,042
(sighs) Oh, God. lt's just so sad.
l can't even believe it.

246
00:22:20,127 --> 00:22:22,118
Footings are too deep.

247
00:22:22,727 --> 00:22:24,524
Got that chain in your truck?

248
00:22:28,807 --> 00:22:30,798
(engine starts)

249
00:22:43,247 --> 00:22:45,238
Hit it!

250
00:22:59,287 --> 00:23:03,519
Our collection of souvenirs
of the Lisbon girls, which still exists,...

251
00:23:03,607 --> 00:23:05,837
..started with Cecilia's diary.

252
00:23:05,927 --> 00:23:09,317
Parkie had gotten it from Skip Ortega,
