lt's all right. That'll do for now.
Give me these. Give me these.

746
01:05:22,967 --> 01:05:24,958
l'll put them in the trash.

747
01:05:31,927 --> 01:05:33,918
(coughs)

748
01:05:43,687 --> 01:05:46,247
(chain saw revs)

749
01:05:56,007 --> 01:05:57,645
(men whoop)

750
01:06:01,127 --> 01:06:04,517
This was the time we began to see Lux
making love on the roof...

751
01:06:04,607 --> 01:06:06,404
..with random boys and men.

752
01:06:06,487 --> 01:06:08,876
- ls she naked?
- You can't tell. Hold on.

753
01:06:08,967 --> 01:06:10,958
Well, get it focused.

754
01:06:11,767 --> 01:06:15,237
- Will you stop? Wait your turn.
- What are they doing?

755
01:06:15,847 --> 01:06:19,362
- They're rolling around up there.
- Let me see. Let me see.

756
01:06:19,447 --> 01:06:23,360
Hold on. And she's on him and
he's rubbing his hands through her hair.

757
01:06:23,447 --> 01:06:27,156
- Come on, let me look.
- No, it's my... lt's my telescope, Chase!

758
01:06:27,247 --> 01:06:29,920
- (laughs)
- Yes, and what else?

759
01:06:30,007 --> 01:06:34,637
Our male up there
seems to be in a Burger Chalet uniform!

760
01:06:36,607 --> 01:06:40,725
That Burger Chalet - you never think
those guys ever get lucky.

761
01:06:41,007 --> 01:06:44,204
She turns to me and asks me
if l thought what we'd done was dirty.

762
01:06:44,287 --> 01:06:46,482
l knew what to say. l said no.

763
01:06:46,567 --> 01:06:49,445
Then she grabs my hand
and goes ''You like me, don't you?''

764
01:06:49,527 --> 01:06:53,202
l didn't say anything.
lt's best to keep chicks guessing.

765
01:06:53,287 --> 01:06:57,326
(woman) Chase, honey!
Come practise your violin before dinner!

766
01:06:59,767 --> 01:07:03,760
You're not gonna believe it.
Lux is on the roof again tonight!

767
01:07:03,847 --> 01:07:06,884
- Her hands are moving down.
- l gotta see this!

768
01:07:07,487 --> 01:07:10,843
- This is beautiful.
- No, no. She's on top of him.

769
01:07:11,607 --> 01:07:13,598
- What's she doin', man?
- Wait.

770
01:07:14,927 --> 01:07:17,077
Now they're done, he's getting up.

771
01:07:19,887 --> 01:07:21,684
- That's it?
- Popcorn.

772
01:07:21,767 --> 01:07:23,166
That was quick.

773
01:07:30,567 --> 01:07:32,558
(mutters)

774
01:07:36,607 --> 01:07:39,724
Ooh, good morning!
Good morning (mumbles plant name)

775
01:07:40,167 --> 01:07:42,556
Have we photosynthesised
breakfast today?

776
01:07:51,287 --> 01:07:53,084
(mutters)

777
01:07:53,167 --> 01:07:55,158
Hello, Ronald.

778
01:07:55,767 --> 01:07:57,359
Hi, Eric.

779
01:07:57,447 --> 01:08:00,757
Your daughters haven't been at school
for over two weeks.

780
01:08:02,887 --> 01:08:04,878
You checked out back?

781
01:08:09,447 --> 01:08:11,836
(woman) They found a new math teacher.

782
01:08:12,687 --> 01:08:15,679
- Well, he's gonna have to get another job.
- l know.

783
01:08:16,807 --> 01:08:20,402
(sighs) How long can those girls
be cooped up like that?

784
01:08:39,927 --> 01:08:42,760
- Just go away. This is our tree.
- Girls!

785
01:08:42,847 --> 01:08:46,283
Girls, it's a little late. This tree is dead.

786
01:08:46,367 --> 01:08:49,882
- Why not leave it up to nature?
- lf we did, there'd be no trees left.

787
01:08:50,367 --> 01:08:52,562
That's what it's gonna be like anyway.

788
01:08:52,647 --> 01:08:56,037
lf boats hadn't brought the fungus,
this wouldn't have happened.

789
01:08:56,127 --> 01:08:58,322
OK? Let's go.

790
01:09:00,327 --> 01:09:01,521
No?

791
01:09:01,967 --> 01:09:03,764
All right. That's it.

792
01:09:03,847 --> 01:09:07,920
l have an order to cut down your elm tree,
but your kids won't let us.

793
01:09:08,007 --> 01:09:12,523
- How do you know that tree's sick?
- lt had yellow leaves. The tree is dead.

794
01:09:12,607 --> 01:09:15,758
Our daughter said Aritex is
a less aggressive therapy.

795
01:09:15,847 --> 01:09:19,522
lt doesn't work. l leave that tree,
they'll all be gone by next year.

796
01:09:19,607 --> 01:09:21,723
Will be anyway, way things are going!

797
01:09:21,807 --> 01:09:24,002
l don't want to call the police.

798
01:09:24,087 --> 01:09:28,922
Our daughters are standing on their own
front lawn. Since when is that a crime?

799
01:09:30,527 --> 01:09:32,119
Right.

800
01:09:32,207 --> 01:09:34,004
(Mr Lisbon) Uh...

801
01:09:43,407 --> 01:09:48,117
Clive, did you see those girls in the
nighties? That's the shot that l want, OK?

802
01:09:48,207 --> 01:09:51,040
Honey, move forward.
l want those girls in the nighties.

803
01:09:51,127 --> 01:09:54,483
Oh, God. OK.
Here, let's just back up a little bit.

804
01:09:56,727 --> 01:09:58,718
There you go. ls that good? OK?

805
01:10:00,327 --> 01:10:03,399
Four sisters of Cecilia Lisbon,
the East Side teenager...

806
01:10:03,487 --> 01:10:07,605
..whose suicide last summer focused
awareness on a national problem,...

807
01:10:07,687 --> 01:10:13,523
..put their own lives in jeopardy by trying
to protect the elm that Cecilia so loved.

808
01:10:13,607 --> 01:10:15,598
(chain saws buzz)

809
01:11:03,687 --> 01:11:06,599
For the next few weeks
we hardly saw the girls at all.

810
01:11:08,887 --> 01:11:12,402
Joe Hill Conley didn't call Therese
as he had promised.

811
01:11:17,167 --> 01:11:19,476
And Lux never spoke to Trip again.

812
01:11:22,767 --> 01:11:24,758
(Trip) You're a stone fox.

813
01:11:29,847 --> 01:11:32,236
The girls' only contact with the outside...

814
01:11:32,327 --> 01:11:36,002
..was through catalogues they ordered
that filled their mailbox...

815
01:11:36,087 --> 01:11:41,559
..with pictures of high-end fashions
and brochures for exotic vacations.

816
01:11:42,247 --> 01:11:44,158
Unable to go anywhere,...

817
01:11:44,247 --> 01:11:48,001
..the girls travelled in their imaginations
to Siamese temples...

818
01:11:48,087 --> 01:11:53,002
..or passed an old man with a leaf broom
tidying a moss-carpeted speck of Japan.

819
01:11:55,207 --> 01:11:57,437
We ordered the same catalogues...

820
01:11:57,527 --> 01:12:01,486
..and, flipping through the pages,
we hiked through passes with the girls,...

821
01:12:01,567 --> 01:12:05,685
..stopping every now and then
to help them with their backpacks,...

822
01:12:05,767 --> 01:12:08,839
..placing our hands
on their warm, moist shoulders...

823
01:12:08,927 --> 01:12:11,680
..and gazing off at papaya sunsets.

824
01:12:13,247 --> 01:12:15,841
We drank tea with them
in a water pavilion.

825
01:12:16,687 --> 01:12:18,678
We did whatever we wanted.

826
01:12:19,967 --> 01:12:23,755
Cecilia hadn't died.
She was a bride in Calcutta.

827
01:12:26,767 --> 01:12:29,122
The only way
we could feel close to the girls...

828
01:12:29,207 --> 01:12:33,962
..was through these impossible trips
which have scarred us forever,...

829
01:12:34,047 --> 01:12:37,437
..making us happier
with dreams than wives.

830
01:12:39,287 --> 01:12:44,122
Collecting everything we could of theirs,
the Lisbon girls wouldn't leave our minds.

831
01:12:44,207 --> 01:12:46,198
But they were slipping away.

832
01:12:46,567 --> 01:12:51,516
The colour of their eyes was fading, along
with the locations of moles and dimples.

833
01:12:51,607 --> 01:12:53,598
From five they had become four,...

834
01:12:53,687 --> 01:12:58,203
..and they were all living in the dead,
becoming shadows.

835
01:12:58,287 --> 01:13:01,757
We'd have lost them completely
if they hadn't contacted us.

836
01:13:01,847 --> 01:13:03,838
OK, one long,...

837
01:13:04,567 --> 01:13:06,444
..two short...

838
01:13:07,047 --> 01:13:09,083
- ..and one long.
- Mm-hm.

839
01:13:09,167 --> 01:13:10,839
You got that? That's it.

840
01:13:14,127 --> 01:13:16,118
''Help.''

841
01:13:16,567 --> 01:13:18,558
''Send...

842
01:13:19,727 --> 01:13:21,558
..bo...

843
01:13:21,647 --> 01:13:23,080
..bo.''

844
01:13:24,967 --> 01:13:26,400
- Bo-bo?
- Bo-bo.

845
01:13:26,487 --> 01:13:29,399
That's what it says: bo-bo.

846
01:13:29,487 --> 01:13:33,605
''Help send bo-bo''?
l thought you knew Morse code.

847
01:14:00,887 --> 01:14:02,878
Something here for you.

848
01:14:10,367 --> 01:14:12,358
l got one, too.

849
01:14:14,607 --> 01:14:17,405
We racked our brains
for a way of contacting them.

850
01:14:17,487 --> 01:14:21,480
Tom Faheem suggested we fly a kite
with a message alongside the house,...

851
01:14:21,567 --> 01:14:23,717
..but that had logistical problems.

852
01:14:23,807 --> 01:14:26,958
ln the end, the answer was so simple
it took a week to work out.

853
01:14:27,527 --> 01:14:29,518
We called them on the telephone.

854
01:14:29,847 --> 01:14:31,439
727...

855
01:14:31,527 --> 01:14:34,519
- ..8221 .
- 8221 .

856
01:14:34,607 --> 01:14:36,802
(whispers) Get ready.

857
01:14:38,847 --> 01:14:41,236
- (Mary) Hello?
- Go!

858
01:14:43,687 --> 01:14:45,917
(Todd Rundgren) * Hello, it's me

859
01:14:48,487 --> 01:14:53,197
* l've thought about us
for a long, long time

860
01:14:53,287 --> 01:14:55,278
Call us. 727 0487.

861
01:15:00,527 --> 01:15:02,916
- (phone rings)
- Shit! lt's them.

862
01:15:08,287 --> 01:15:11,199
(Gilbert O'Sullivan)
* To think that only yesterday

863
01:15:11,287 --> 01:15:13,676
* l was cheerful, bright and gay

864
01:15:13,767 --> 01:15:16,235
* Looking forward to - who wouldn't do? -

865
01:15:16,327 --> 01:15:19,000
* The role l was about to play

866
01:15:19,087 --> 01:15:21,647
* But in my hour of need

867
01:15:21,727 --> 01:15:24,161
* l truly am indeed

868
01:15:24,247 --> 01:15:26,124
* Alone again

869
01:15:26,687 --> 01:15:28,086
* Naturally

870
01:15:28,167 --> 01:15:34,003
(The Bee Gees)
* Run to me whenever you're lonely

871
01:15:34,087 --> 01:15:40,083
* Run to me if you need a shoulder

872
01:15:40,167 --> 01:15:46,481
* Now and then you need someone older

873
01:15:46,567 --> 01:15:48,797
* So darling

874
01:15:48,887 --> 01:15:52,402
(Carole King) * So far away

875
01:15:52,487 --> 01:15:58,483
* Doesn't anybody stay
in one place any more?

876
01:15:58,887 --> 01:16:04,564
* lt would be so fine
to see your face at my door

877
01:16:05,647 --> 01:16:12,359
* Doesn't help to know you're just far

878
01:16:12,447 --> 01:16:14,403
* Away

879
01:16:14,487 --> 01:16:16,478
l gotta go home. See ya tomorrow.

880
01:16:16,967 --> 01:16:18,958
l'll see you later.

881
01:16:22,527 --> 01:16:25,724
- (Lux) We're suffocating.
- (Mrs Lisbon) You're safe here.

882
01:16:25,807 --> 01:16:27,604
l can't breathe in here.

883
01:16:29,247 --> 01:16:31,238
No answer.

884
01:16:52,247 --> 01:16:54,636
- (Tim) What time is it?
- (Chase) Any time now.

885
01:16:55,367 --> 01:16:57,562
- Guys, there it is.
- What?

886
01:17:01,367 --> 01:17:03,597
(Tim) Yeah, it's them.

887
01:17:04,487 --> 01:17:06,478
(all) Let's go!

888
01:17:17,447 --> 01:17:19,836
(whispers) l have keys to my mom's car.

889
01:17:27,327 --> 01:17:29,716
- (clatter)
- Shh!

890
01:17:42,967 --> 01:17:44,958
Maybe we should knock.

891
01:17:47,007 --> 01:17:48,201
(knocks)

892
01:17:50,447 --> 01:17:51,641
We're here.

893
01:18:01,647 --> 01:18:03,638
About time.

894
01:18:03,727 --> 01:18:05,718
We've been waiting for you guys.

895
01:18:06,247 --> 01:18:09,523
We got a car, a full tank.
We'll take you anywhere you wanna go.

896
01:18:09,607 --> 01:18:11,882
lt's just a Cougar, but it's got a big trunk.

897
01:18:12,407 --> 01:18:13,999
Can l sit up front?

898
01:18:15,487 --> 01:18:16,886
Sure.

899
01:18:19,447 --> 01:18:22,598
Which one of you
is gonna sit up front next to me?

900
01:18:23,927 --> 01:18:25,519
Where are your parents?

901
01:18:26,407 --> 01:18:27,806
Asleep.

902
01:18:27,887 --> 01:18:31,163
- What about your sisters?
- They're coming.

903
01:18:31,967 --> 01:18:34,322
Come on, it's getting late.

904
01:18:35,527 --> 01:18:39,406
Wait five minutes. We had to wait
until my parents were asleep.

905
01:18:39,487 --> 01:18:43,082
They take for ever.
My mom's an insomniac.

906
01:18:47,047 --> 01:18:49,641
We better take our car.
There's more room.

907
01:18:51,247 --> 01:18:53,442
Think you can handle a station wagon?

908
01:18:54,487 --> 01:18:57,399
Sure. lt's not a stick, is it?

909
01:18:57,487 --> 01:18:59,876
- No.
- Yeah, no problem.

910
01:19:00,127 --> 01:19:03,358
- Will you let me steer?
- Sure.

911
01:19:03,727 --> 01:19:06,844
But maybe we should go.
l heard somethin'. Could be your mom.

912
01:19:07,567 --> 01:19:09,558
Come on in.

913
01:19:19,127 --> 01:19:23,086
l'll go wait in the car.
You guys wait here for my sisters.

914
01:19:40,447 --> 01:19:42,438
(girls giggling)

915
01:19:47,407 --> 01:19:49,523
(humming)

916
01:19:53,967 --> 01:19:55,764
(thud)

917
01:20:16,927 --> 01:20:20,715
These girls are making me crazy.
lf l could feel one of 'em up just once...

918
01:20:24,207 --> 01:20:25,799
What?

919
01:20:29,607 --> 01:20:31,404
(creaking)

920
01:20:31,487 --> 01:20:33,478
(hissing)

921
01:20:42,487 --> 01:20:45,684
We would never be sure
about the sequence of events.

922
01:20:46,167 --> 01:20:48,158
We argue about it still.

923
01:20:51,167 --> 01:20:54,842
Most likely Bonnie had died while we
were waiting in the living room,...

924
01:20:54,927 --> 01:20:56,918
..dreaming of highways.

925
01:20:57,927 --> 01:21:00,964
Mary put her head in the oven
shortly thereafter.

926
01:21:01,687 --> 01:21:06,158
Therese, stuffed with sleeping pills,
was gone by the time we got there.

927
01:21:06,887 --> 01:21:08,639
Lux was the last to go.

928
01:21:08,727 --> 01:21:10,718
(engine running)

929
01:21:12,287 --> 01:21:14,084
(coughs)

930
01:21:18,047 --> 01:21:22,165
lt's four o'clock on Sunday afternoon.
Do you know where your children are?

931
01:21:22,247 --> 01:21:25,239
(reporters' voices overlapping)

932
01:21:30,607 --> 01:21:32,598
(babble of voices)

933
01:21:37,367 --> 01:21:40,962
This has been Lydia Perl
with Channel 8 News.

934
01:21:49,807 --> 01:21:53,197
(Mrs Lisbon) None of my daughters
lacked for any love.

935
01:21:54,607 --> 01:21:57,280
There was plenty of love in our house.

936
01:21:59,047 --> 01:22:01,242
l never understood why...

937
01:22:31,887 --> 01:22:37,280
After the suicide free-for-all the Lisbons
gave up any attempt to lead a normal life.

938
01:22:39,527 --> 01:22:42,121
They had Mr Hedlie pack up the house,...

939
01:22:42,207 --> 01:22:45,244
..selling what furniture he could
in a garage sale.

940
01:22:47,487 --> 01:22:49,876
Mr Lisbon put the house on the market...

941
01:22:49,967 --> 01:22:52,765
..and it was sold to
a young couple from Boston.

942
01:22:53,367 --> 01:22:57,201
We, of course, took the family photos
that were put out with the trash.

943
01:22:57,287 --> 01:22:58,845
(clock ticking)

944
01:23:00,127 --> 01:23:04,837
We had pieces of the puzzle, but however
we put them together, gaps remained -

945
01:23:05,527 --> 01:23:09,156
..oddly shaped emptiness,
mapped by what surrounded them...

946
01:23:09,247 --> 01:23:11,477
..like countries we couldn't name.

947
01:23:14,727 --> 01:23:21,075
What lingered after them was not life,
but the most trivial list of mundane facts.:

948
01:23:24,127 --> 01:23:26,197
..a clock ticking on the wall,...

949
01:23:27,367 --> 01:23:29,562
..a room dim at noon,...

950
01:23:30,647 --> 01:23:35,038
..the outrageousness of a human being
thinking only of herself.

951
01:23:39,527 --> 01:23:43,122
We began the impossible process
of trying to forget them.

952
01:23:49,527 --> 01:23:52,678
Our parents seemed
better able to do this,...

953
01:23:52,767 --> 01:23:55,884
..returning to their tennis foursomes
and cocktail cruises...

954
01:23:55,967 --> 01:23:59,004
..as though they'd seen this all before.

955
01:23:59,447 --> 01:24:04,601
lt was full-fledged summer again, over
a year since Cecilia had slit her wrists,...

956
01:24:04,687 --> 01:24:07,155
..spreading the poison in the air.

957
01:24:07,247 --> 01:24:10,319
A spill at the plant
increased the phosphates in the lake...

958
01:24:10,407 --> 01:24:14,525
..and produced a scum of algae so thick
that the swamp smell filled the air,...

959
01:24:14,607 --> 01:24:17,041
..infiltrating the genteel mansions.

960
01:24:18,007 --> 01:24:21,682
Debutantes cried over the misfortune
of coming out in a season...

961
01:24:21,767 --> 01:24:24,600
..everyone would remember
for its bad smell.

962
01:24:24,687 --> 01:24:28,600
The O'Conners, however,
came up with the ingenious solution...

963
01:24:28,687 --> 01:24:32,760
..of making the theme of their daughter
Alice's debutante party ''Asphyxiation''.

964
01:24:32,847 --> 01:24:36,635
Like everyone else,
we went to forget about the Lisbon girls.

965
01:24:37,687 --> 01:24:39,882
(woman) She'll give him a heart attack!

966
01:24:46,607 --> 01:24:48,598
(muffled voices)

967
01:25:08,207 --> 01:25:10,198
(muffled voices)

968
01:25:23,127 --> 01:25:25,118
Hi, Parkie.

969
01:25:25,647 --> 01:25:27,444
(vomits)

970
01:25:29,287 --> 01:25:31,676
Al's got the acting bug, you know.

971
01:25:33,247 --> 01:25:35,442
- She caught it from Pinkie.
- (laughter)

972
01:25:36,567 --> 01:25:39,639
And l want to announce tonight
that next fall...

973
01:25:39,727 --> 01:25:42,924
..Alice is going to
a little school in New Haven(!)

974
01:25:43,807 --> 01:25:45,525
(laughter)

975
01:25:45,607 --> 01:25:48,724
l hear they have
a great drama school out there.

976
01:25:48,807 --> 01:25:52,846
- ln fact, Sam, didn't your father build it?
- That's the law school.

977
01:25:54,527 --> 01:25:58,122
We're so proud of Alice.
We really couldn't be prouder.

978
01:25:58,487 --> 01:26:00,478
(all toast)

979
01:26:05,927 --> 01:26:08,077
l've had it.

980
01:26:08,167 --> 01:26:10,283
Goodbye, cruel world.

981
01:26:16,087 --> 01:26:18,760
No, no, no, you don't understand me!

982
01:26:18,847 --> 01:26:21,236
l'm a teenager. l got problems!

983
01:26:22,007 --> 01:26:23,998
(laughter)

984
01:26:31,407 --> 01:26:34,205
So much has been said
